
Tech Stack:

Frontend:
- Next.js 15 App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Shadcn UI
- TanStack Query
- Axios
- React Hook Form
- Zod

Backend:
- FastAPI
- PostgreSQL
- SQLAlchemy Async
- Alembic
- JWT Authentication
- Redis
- Celery

Architecture:

Frontend:
UI Layer
→ Feature Layer
→ Service Layer
→ API Layer

Backend:
Router Layer
→ Service Layer
→ Repository Layer
→ Database Layer

==================================================
GENERAL RULES
==================================================

- Always write production-grade code.
- Never write demo code.
- Never use placeholder implementations.
- Follow SOLID principles.
- Follow Clean Architecture principles.
- Keep code modular and reusable.
- Use dependency injection whenever possible.
- Prefer composition over inheritance.
- Avoid code duplication.
- Use strict TypeScript.
- Use async/await consistently.
- Use meaningful variable names.

==================================================
BACKEND RULES
==================================================

FastAPI routers must:

- Contain routing logic only.
- Never contain business logic.
- Never contain SQL queries.

Services must:

- Contain business logic.
- Handle validation.
- Handle authorization.
- Call repositories.

Repositories must:

- Contain database access logic only.
- Never contain business rules.

Use:

- SQLAlchemy Async
- AsyncSession
- Repository Pattern
- Service Pattern

All APIs must:

- Return consistent responses.
- Use Pydantic schemas.
- Include proper status codes.
- Include error handling.

Authentication:

- JWT access token
- Role-based access control
- bcrypt password hashing

Database:

- PostgreSQL
- UUID primary keys
- Proper foreign keys
- Proper indexes

Migrations:

- Use Alembic only.
- Never modify existing migrations.

Testing:

- Use pytest.
- Create unit tests for services.
- Create integration tests for APIs.

==================================================
FRONTEND RULES
==================================================

Use:

- Server Components by default.
- Client Components only when necessary.

Forms:

- React Hook Form
- Zod validation

API Calls:

- TanStack Query
- Axios

Components:

- Keep components small.
- Prefer reusable components.
- Separate UI from business logic.

Do not:

- Fetch data directly inside UI components.
- Place API logic inside components.
- Duplicate state.

==================================================
FOLDER STRUCTURE
==================================================

Frontend:

src/
├── app/
├── components/
├── features/
├── services/
├── hooks/
├── lib/
├── providers/
├── types/

Backend:

app/
├── api/
├── core/
├── db/
├── models/
├── schemas/
├── repositories/
├── services/
├── chatbot/
├── middleware/
├── tasks/
├── utils/

==================================================
NAMING CONVENTIONS
==================================================

Files:
snake_case

Examples:

auth_service.py
consultation_repository.py

Classes:
PascalCase

Examples:

AuthService
ConsultationRepository

Functions:
snake_case

Examples:

create_consultation()
get_consultations()

Variables:
snake_case

Constants:
UPPER_SNAKE_CASE

==================================================
ERROR HANDLING
==================================================

Backend:

- Use custom exceptions.
- Never expose internal errors.
- Return structured API errors.

Frontend:

- Show user-friendly errors.
- Handle loading states.
- Handle empty states.

==================================================
CHATBOT MODULE
==================================================

Intent classification must be separated from database logic.

Structure:

chatbot/
├── intent_classifier.py
├── sql_resolver.py
├── response_builder.py

Never place chatbot logic inside routers.

==================================================
SECURITY
==================================================

Never:

- Store plain-text passwords.
- Expose secrets.
- Hardcode credentials.
- Disable validation.

Always:

- Validate inputs.
- Sanitize outputs.
- Verify permissions.
- Use environment variables.

==================================================
CODE GENERATION
==================================================

When generating code:

1. Explain architecture briefly.
2. Generate complete code.
3. Include imports.
4. Include typing.
5. Follow project structure.
6. Follow repository-service pattern.
7. Follow production standards.